<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-02-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-02-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="9" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d9">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 1012/6.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Chargé <persName type="to">Brown</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-02-28"><hi rend="italic">February 28,
                                    1907</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 327.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to Mr. Coombs’s No. 516 of the
                            23d ultimo, I inclose a copy of a note from the Chinese minister at
                            Washington, expressing his appreciation of the action of the legation in
                            obtaining redress for a Chinese subject who had been assaulted by a
                            Guatemalan policeman.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">E. Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>